body.raw: import { Button } from 'ui'; import { Alert } from 'ui'; import { AlertCircleIcon, SparkleIcon, GithubIcon } from 'lucide-react'; # Button The `Button` element in web development is an HTML element used to create interactive buttons that users can click or tap to trigger specific actions or functions on a web page. The ` ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ## Props We have such of props that make you able to customize button as you like. Below you will find more examples about how to use this props, and what each one of them is going to do. ### Colors Our `Button` component have many color options. Which are `default` | `error` | `warning` | `success`. Each one of these values is referencing to a color. If you want to change these default colors check [`How to customize themes in @Geeks/UI`](#) ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Variants You can change the style of button by playing with `variant` prop. Which can accept follow values: `solid` | `bordered` | `light` | `ghost` | `flat` | `shadow` ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Sizes You can change size of your buttons based on this prop. Which allows you control the size of your `Button` component by passing one of these values: `sm` (Small) | `md` (Medium) | `lg` (Large) ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Radiuses Also you are able to change `border-radius` of your button with `radius` props: `sm` | `md` | `lg` | `circle` | `none`. ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ``` ### Icon Only Use the `iconOnly` prop to create a button with only an icon. You can use any of icons library or custom SVGs. } description={We recommend using `lucide-react` icons library. Has a huge of nice icons. } /> ```jsx showLineNumbers import {Button} from 'ui'; ```
